.SH NAME
cert-expiry - Display certificate expiry date


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBcert expiry  [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
Display the expiry date of a certificate file. If quiet mode is enabled,
only certificates expiring within the window are displayed.


.SH OPTIONS
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for expiry

.PP
\fB-p\fP, \fB--leeway\fP=2160h0m0s
	leeway for certificate expiry checks (e.g. 1h30m

.PP
\fB--short\fP[=false]
	short certificate names


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
\fB--ca\fP=""
